{
  "texts": [
    "Despite the success of these strategies, each method has its limitations.",
    "Informativeness-based methods, while focusing on selecting samples with the highest uncertainty, often overlook that not all diverse samples are equally beneficial for training.",
    "Representativenessbased methods enhance the model's generalization ability by exposing it to diverse examples but might miss informative yet rare instances.",
    "Hybrid approaches, though aiming to balance these two criteria, often introduce increased complexity and computational costs.",
    "Our work aims to develop novel active learning strategies that address these limitations, maintaining high performance in image classification tasks."
  ]
}